Coca-Cola Plans $25 Billion Investment in 5 Years, Hurriyet Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-05-07T10:11:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-07/coca-cola-plans-25-billion-investment-in-5-years-hurriyet-says.html
Coca-Cola Co. (KO) , the world’s largest
soft-drink maker, plans to invest more than $25 billion over the
next 5 years to help reach its $200 billion sales target in
2020,  Hurriyet  reported, citing chief executive  Muhtar Kent .  Turkey is among the “tigers” of growth markets for the
company, which also include  Brazil , Russia, India and China,
Kent said, according to an interview with the Istanbul-based
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 